# Copy this to .env.e2e and fill in your values.
# .env.e2e is gitignored — never commit real secrets.

# ── Third-party OAuth (for external auth e2e tests) ─────────────────────
# These need a real OAuth app registered with the provider.
# The e2e test mocks the provider's endpoints so no real API calls are made,
# but the OAuth dance (browser, callback, token exchange) is fully exercised.

# Google example:
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-client-secret

# ── Atlassian (for real API e2e tests) ───────────────────────────────────
# ATLASSIAN_SITE=mysite.atlassian.net
# ATLASSIAN_EMAIL=you@example.com
# ATLASSIAN_API_TOKEN=ATATT3x...
